This paper is about image super-resolution using deep convolutional networks, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of very deep networks and the training procedure, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper presents visual improvements in the results, which could be considered multimedia (cs.MM).
